content.text: The ElizaOS project has seen significant development with multiple new plugins and improvements. Key updates include the addition of the NVIDIA NIM Plugin, which integrates NVIDIA AI Foundation Models for content analysis and safety checks. This plugin introduces six specialized actions, including AI Image Detection, DeepFake Detection, and Jailbreak Detection. The implementation includes TypeScript-based development, robust error handling, and detailed documentation.

A new Router Nitro Plugin was introduced to facilitate cross-chain token swaps and bridging using the Router Nitro Bridge. Initially supporting EVM chains, the plugin is designed for future expansion to non-EVM chains. It includes robust error handling, agent configuration enhancements, and utility functions for chain and token interactions.

The Cronos EVM Plugin was added, supporting Cronos Mainnet and Testnet. It enables token transfers, balance checking, and wallet provider implementation. Enhancements include validation schemas for balance and transfer actions, improved error handling, and security guidelines for key management.

The HoldStation Wallet Plugin was introduced, allowing token swapping on Hold.so. It currently supports the ZKsync Era blockchain, with Berachain support planned. The plugin enables wallet portfolio fetching, token allowance checks, and transaction approvals.

A TRON blockchain plugin was implemented, supporting native token transfers, cross-chain bridging via Symbiosis, token swapping on SunSwap, and wallet balance tracking. The plugin includes custom RPC endpoint configuration and integrates with the Eliza agent framework.

The OmniFlix Plugin was introduced, integrating the OmniFlix Network with ElizaOS. It supports wallet management, staking operations (delegation, redelegation, undelegation), and token transfers. The plugin includes environment variable configurations and detailed testing steps.

The Merlin Plugin was added, enabling Bitcoin Layer1 token creation and BTCFun functionality through Merlin. It integrates with the Eliza agent for seamless user experience and supports enhanced scalability for Bitcoin-based applications.

A new Email Plugin was introduced, allowing Eliza agents to send and receive emails. This feature enhances automation capabilities for customer support, workflow processing, and business communications.

The Suno AI Music Generation Plugin was developed, enabling AI-powered music creation and audio manipulation. Features include generating music from text prompts, custom music creation, and extending existing audio tracks.

The Udio AI Music Generation Plugin was introduced, integrating Udio AIâ€™s capabilities into ElizaOS. It allows users to generate music from text prompts, extend audio tracks, and create custom compositions with fine-tuned parameters.

Bug fixes and improvements were made across multiple plugins, including resolving chat errors in the OpenAI plugin, fixing a typo in the Conflux plugin, and addressing boolean parsing issues in the OpenAI Community Plugin setting.

ElizaOS has announced multiple integrations, expanding its reach across various blockchain and AI platforms. It is now live on @0xPolygon, @StoryProtocol, @MerlinLayer2, and integrated with @thirdweb's Nebula and @trondao. Additionally, users can launch their ElizaOS agent on @fleek in just 30 seconds.
ElizaOS has also partnered with AgentKit by @coinbase, @hyperbolic_labs, and @bebop_dex, further strengthening its ecosystem.

Official SimsAI Release V1.0: Eliza agents now integrate with SimsAI's Jeeter social network, enabling them to post, monitor, and engage in conversations. This update enhances Eliza's social capabilities, allowing AI agents to interact in a public social space. The integration includes JeeterPostClient, JeeterSearchClient, and JeeterInteractionClient, ensuring agents can post, search, and respond effectively. Developers can configure agents with specific tones, knowledge, and conversational hooks. The update also introduces new documentation and testing guidelines for seamless deployment.

SIMSAI OFFICIAL RELEASE (ElizaOS changes made): This update further refines the SimsAI integration, enhancing Eliza agents' ability to engage in social interactions on the Jeeter platform. The release introduces new character profiles, improved error handling, and additional configuration options. Key features include automated posting, real-time engagement, and expanded character capabilities. The update positions Eliza as a leading AI social agent framework, with potential for future integrations beyond Jeeter.

categories.title: Recent Updates and Fixes in ElizaOS Repository

content.text: The integration tests workflow has been updated with improved caching and standardized installation commands. Key changes include adding pnpm cache configuration using actions/cache@v4, using --frozen-lockfile for deterministic installations, removing redundant cleanup steps, and simplifying branch configuration syntax. The update ensures that required environment variables (OPENAI_API_KEY and COINBASE_COMMERCE_KEY) are maintained. Testing has verified that the changes align with best practices.

A bug has been reported where integration tests fail in CI despite running successfully locally. The failure occurs during the build step due to a DTS Build error, preventing the tests from executing. The issue affects all new PRs.
A fix has been implemented for build and test issues in the develop branch. The holdstation plugin was temporarily removed, and build issues affecting other plugins were addressed.
Tests and configuration updates have been added for the plugin-agentkit provider.

categories.title: Issues with `@elizaos/agent` Installation and Vite Security Updates

content.text: The `@elizaos/agent` npm package cannot be installed due to missing dependencies. Errors include a 404 fetch error for `@elizaos/adapter-pglite` and a workspace package not found error for `@elizaos/plugin-avail`. These issues prevent successful installation.

A security update for the Vite dependency addresses CVE-2025-24010, which allowed unauthorized access to the development server due to permissive CORS settings and lack of validation on the Origin header for WebSocket connections. The update introduces stricter security measures, including limiting CORS origins, validating WebSocket connections, and restricting access based on allowed hosts.

content.text: DAOVOS #1 was a success, and the event will continue with DAOVOS #2 featuring @theTBTFdao. Viewers are encouraged to set reminders for the next session.
@DegenSpartanAI was accused of spreading misinformation, while the @pillzumi team was defended against rug pull allegations. The situation was clarified, stating that the team remains trustworthy.
A discussion on blockchain ecosystems emphasized that most people are not strictly Solana or Ethereum maximalists. Instead, they prioritize user needs and build where users are present.

A recent update to the ElizaOS client-farcaster introduced new test configurations and coverage, including tests for casting, client interactions, and utilities. Additionally, a test for like iteration was added.

Users have reported an issue where the client application fails to load after setting up a fresh clone of ElizaOS. The agent console runs correctly, but the client app displays an error, resulting in an empty screen. The issue occurs on macOS 14.6.1 (M2).

Another reported issue involves the inability to connect to the GROQ model provider. While the agent initializes successfully and services register correctly, the client UI does not display any agents and continuously switches between 'connect...' and 'disconnected'.

A feature request has been proposed to add a Sequelize database client to ElizaOS. This would provide an ORM-based approach for database operations, improving maintainability and testability while keeping the existing PostgreSQL adapter intact. The Sequelize client would offer model-based operations, connection pooling, and better TypeScript integration.
